cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.HC

This paper is about training a neural network using CUDA to predict blood glucose control from non-invasive markers. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves machine learning and optimization, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The use of non-invasive markers involves computer vision techniques, which makes cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves data analysis and healthcare applications, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) possible sub-categories.
